OL,3,CUK should sign climate change co-
OL,4,Coperation agreement with China, says
OL,5,Cthink tank
OL,7,FIn a paper due to be published next
OL,8,Fweek, Chatham House said a formal deal
OL,9,Fwould enable "bolder and more
OL,10,Fconfident engagement" by the UK in
OL,11,FChina "and vice versa", allowing the
OL,12,Ftwo countries to better share
OL,13,Fexpertise.
OL,15,FChris Aylett, one of the paper's
OL,16,Fauthors, said China could benefit from
OL,17,Fthe UK's "considerable success
OL,18,Fbringing down its own emissions" and
OL,19,Foffered a "huge" potential, given the
OL,20,Fcountry accounted for nearly a third
OL,21,Fof global emissions.
